spans.text: — MACBETH , the victor of the field , Exulting , past the blasted wild ; And where his dark overhanging towers Frown on the heath , with
the hours — Sweet are the rosy beams that chase The angry tempest from the sky
the hours — Sweet are the rosy beams
Whose grateful rapture sooths the toil of arms
All the rapid torrents might , When with turbulence they sweep , Mingling , with the winds of might , Sounds majestically deep — When nature formed the hideous waste
Chill with dread the human frame , Then unreal shapes
By the blue unhallowed flame — Discordance strange disturbs the gentle air , And poisonous taints the thickening breezes bear
threw the shadow's lengthening line At solemn distance far below
stood a venerable seer , Whose prophetic soul could trace Distant ages hastening near , And all that filled the unborn space
Have ! — dread visions hang in air !
See the look , and hear the groan
a lyre , whose source sublime With wonder thrills the listening earth
